text: Melicope kaalaensis is a species of plant in the family Rutaceae known by the common name Kaala melicope. I It is endemic to the Waianae Range on Oahu island, in the Hawaiian Islands. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== kaalaensis Category:Endemic flora of Hawaii Category:Biota of Oahu Category:Waianae Range Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
